        <body>
            <pb n="2" facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Extent and Pop@ation of America.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rendition="#k">London,</hi> Oct. 17</dateline>
                <p>&#x2014;The following es<lb break="yes"/>timate of the extent, in square league@,<lb break="yes"/>and population, of the continent of<lb break="yes" />America in 1822, was lately transmitted<lb break="yes"/>by Baron de, Humboldt from Paris, to<lb break="yes"/>President Boliv@, with the accompany-<lb break="no"/>ing letter:</p>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2"> </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Sq. Leagues.</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Population</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Mexico or New Spain</cell>
                        <cell>75330</cell>
                        <cell>6300000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Gautimala</cell>
                        <cell>16740</cell>
                        <cell>1600000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Cuba and Puerto-Rico</cell>
                        <cell>44@0</cell>
                        <cell>@00000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell rows="2" rendition="#rightBraced">Colombia</cell>
                        <cell>Venezuela</cell>
                        <cell>3@600</cell>
                        <cell>900000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>New Grenada</cell>
                        <cell>58250</cell>
                        <cell>1800000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Peru</cell>
                        <cell>42210</cell>
                        <cell>1400000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Chile</cell>
                        <cell>14240</cell>
                        <cell>1100000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Buenos Ayres</cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#u">126770</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#u">2000000</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Total formerly Spanish</cell>
                        <cell>372110</cell>
                        <cell>16400000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">United States</cell>
                        <cell>125440</cell>
                        <cell>10200000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Brazil</cell>
                        <cell>256990</cell>
                        <cell>4000000</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The above surfaces have been calcu-<lb break="no"/>lated with great care, on maps rectified<lb break="yes"/>by astronomical observations. The<lb break="yes" />c@lculations have been several times<lb break="yes"/>repeated by M. Mathieu Member of the<lb break="yes"/>Board of Longitude and of the Institute,<lb break="yes"/>as well as by myself. The results dif-<lb break="no"/>fer from those published in 1819 in the<lb break="yes"/>political essay on Mexico. Then the<lb break="yes"/>inhabited parts alone had been calcula-<lb break="no" />ted, without including the desert legion<lb break="yes"/>over which the independent @bes of<lb break="yes"/>the indigenous inhabi@ wander.&#x2014;<lb break="yes"/>Now the whole extent of each country,<lb break="yes"/>to @ furthest limits has been measured.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The population of the different parts<lb break="yes"/>of <hi rendition="#i" >cidevant</hi> Spanish America is ur cer-<lb break="no"/>tain, nevertheless eách portion has been<lb break="yes"/>calculated according to the latest dates,<lb break="yes"/>which have reached me. The present<lb break="yes" />est@mate ought to be considered in the<lb break="yes"/>same light as all my other works on A-<lb break="no"/>merica; they are no other than essays, in<lb break="yes"/>which every thing will have to be done<lb break="yes"/>over again. Statistical calculations can<lb break="yes"/>only be rendered perfect by degrees, in<lb break="yes"/>in like manner as the elements of inete-<lb break="no"/>orological and astronomical tables.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Comparison.</hi>&#x2014;Spain contains 16,094<lb break="yes" />square leagues&#x2014;Europe contains 304,-<lb break="no"/>710 square leagues, and the whole of<lb break="yes"/>Southern Ameri&#x00E7;a, 581,891 square<lb break="yes"/>leagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">
                            <hi rendition="#k">Humboldt.</hi>
                        </hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
